checkmating on g2.} 26. Be3 Qxc3 27. Bd4 (27. Rc1 Qb2 $1 {Just in time, Black
has this counterattacking move because the a2-bishop is hanging. Thus,
everything is under control.}) 27... Qc6 {Black has a slight advantage, but
the game ended in a draw afterwards.} 28. f3 Qg6 29. Qxg6 Nxg6 30. h4 h5 31.
